r of the investment services firm american realty capital he is often characterized as a pioneer in the alternative investment sector of the financial services industry particularly due to his influence on the commercial real estate investment space he has received a number of honors and public recognition for his impact on the industry including the ernst  young entrepreneur of the year award in  and the ernst  young entrepreneur of the year lifetime achievement award in  he is also regarded as one of the principal figures contributing to the increased appeal and accessibility of commercial real estate investments to individual investors contents  early life  early career  ar capital and american realty capital trust  realty capital securities  new york reit  arc healthcare trust listing and sale  rcs capital corporation  business approach  personal life  philanthropy  references early lifeedit schorsch was born in philadelphia pennsylvania to irvin g schorsch jr and anita née ulick schorsch schorsch went to work for his family’s scrap metal business at the age of  while attending drexel university fulltime before taking over ownership of the business entirely within six years schorsch grew the business into a multimilliondollar enterprise eventually selling it for a profit of  million at age  he next founded thermal reduction corporation a metal product manufacturing business over ten years he successfully built up this company through a series of mergers and acquisitions eventually selling his interests to corrpro in  early careeredit in  he and his wife shelley cofounded the jenkintownbased american financial resource group which originally acquired operating companies in the printing label and financial services sector within two years the company diversified into the acquisition of commercial real estate properties in  schorsch learned of a merger between corestates financial corporation a bank with whom he did business and first union corporation as a result of the pending merger  of corestates’ bank branches were set to close upon hearing this schorsch immediately offered to buy every single vacant bank branch building schorsch recalled in a  interview which appeared in the business section of the new york times “they the bank thought i was a crazy man” however the  million deal was successfully completed within  days and within just  months he had sold or leased  of the properties in  american financial resource group became american financial realty trust or afrt schorsch served as the company’s president ceo and vice chairman of the board of trustees listing it publicly on the new york stock exchange in  shortly after schorsch was dubbed “the bankers landlord” by the philadelphia inquirer in  schorsch left afrt ar capital and american realty capital trustedit schorsch moved to new york city in  where he along with william m “bill” kahane founded the investment services firm american realty capital later renamed to ar capital as the sponsor expanded into alternative investments vehicles other than commercial real estate shortly thereafter the ar capital partnership expanded to include michael weil president and chief operating officer peter budko executive vice president and chief investment officer and brian block executive vice president and chief financial officer ar capital’s flagship investment program was named american realty capital trust inc or arct similar to american financial realty trust arct would invest in single tenant commercial real estate properties leased to corporate businesses that provided other essential goods and services such as walgreens cvs dollar general advanced auto parts and federal express in march  american realty capital trust inc listed on the nasdaq providing liquidity for its shareholders schorsch served as chairman of the company from inception until january  when it merged with realty income corporation nyse o realty capital securitiesedit in  the five partners of ar capital used their own funds to create realty capital securities llc or rcs a broker dealer seven times larger than any other brokerdealer operating in the industry at the time furthermore they launched not one but a series of investment programs simultaneously using the brokerdealer platform to raise capital for other sponsor companies in the industry this would save sponsors the time cost and risk of building their own brokerdealer as well as generate substantial profit for rcs in june  realty capital securities announced that it had reached another milestone  billion of raised equity since inception this coincided with realty capital securities garnering a  market share in the real estate managing brokerdealer sales more than five times that of the next competitor new york reitedit on april   new york recovery reit inc one of schorschs nontraded reit programs became new york reit nysenyrt the first traded reit to acquire real estate exclusively in new york city the portfolio consists of  billion worth of new york city properties notably a  billion  stake in one worldwide plaza a mixed use residential and commercial complex earlier in the year the fund managed to acquire an office building at  broadway pushing into the times square submarket as well as the leasehold interest in the viceroy hotel arc healthcare trust listing and saleedit on april   schorsch listed yet another of his companies american realty capital healthcare trust inc on the nasdaq exchange at  per share nasdaqhct in january  this medicalrelated property portfolio was purchased by ventas inc nyse vtr in an approximately  billion transaction or at  per hct share rcs capital corporationedit in  schorsch along with the ar capital partnership united their brokerdealer investment banking transfer agency and transaction management companies under one holding company named rcs capital corporation this was made available for public ownership in june  when rcs capital corporation successfully closed its initial public offering and listed on the new york stock exchange nyse rcap shortly after rcaps ipo schorch announced the acquisition of first allied holdings inc together with the legend group serving over  independent financial advisors on october   rcs capital announced the acquisition of the hatteras funds group whose principal business is acting as sponsor investment adviser and distributor of a family of mutual fund companies on october   rcs capital announced the acquisition of investors capital holdings ltd an independent brokerdealer and investment advisory services firm – a fourtime winner of investment advisor’s brokerdealer of the year award on november  rcs capital announced the acquisition of asset management and investment advisory services firm summit financial services group inc on january   rcs capital announced that it had agreed to purchase cetera financial group and on january   announced its similar intention to acquire jp turner  company for  billion and  million respectively an article by investment news cited that if all his deals come to fruitionhis network would have close to  registered representatives and financial advisers producing about  billion in total annual revenue placing him in the top tier of independent brokerdealers on april   rcap announced that it had officially completed its acquisition of cetera financial group on june   the company completed its acquisition of summit financial services group two days later on june   rcs capital completed yet another of its previously announced independent brokerdealer acquisitions closing on jp turner  company as reported by yahoo finance the rcs capital share price rose to over  per share in  prior to reports of massive insider selling of rcap later a trade journal investment news in  disclosed a report of the directors of various non traded reits affiliated with the firm had been cashing out of their insider shares using the  redemption privilege built into the terms of the offerings by late  rca