orsch is married to shelley davis schorsch and together they have five children he is an avid collector of american muscle cars high performance cars and foreign sports cars he is also an art collector favoring colonial american art and antiques as well as modern art philanthropyedit nicholas schorsch his wife shelley and his family support the following academic institutions charitable causes and charitable foundations the gateway middle school – nicholas schorsch serves on the board of trustees for the gateway middle school which he helped found in  along with his wife shelley he is a contributor to the school’s events and activities drexel university – a drexel university alumnus schorsch joined the board of trustees where his duties as board member include engaging in the strategic planning process of the university hearts of gold – nicholas schorsch is a member of the advisory board and former honorary chair of the charitable organization hearts of gold which fosters a sustainable change in lifestyle and levels of selfsufficiency for nyc’s homeless mothers and their children in  schorsch was honored with the hearts of gold’s angel of the year award for his supporting the organization historic williamsburg mount pleasant – in  nicholas and shelley bought the historic  acre mount pleasant plantation and worked toward restoring its historic appearance following the restoration of the property they created the mount pleasant foundation to preserve support and share with the general public the rich historical resources of the area in may  they opened their home to visitors as part of the tour of thomas jefferson’s life the hewitt school – nicholas schorsch is a member of the board of trustees for the hewitt school an independent school for girls grades k sarah lawrence college – the alma mater of nicholas schorsch jr shelley and nicholas support sarah lawrence college where shelly also formerly served as a trustee abington friends school – schorsch served as an assistant clerk assistant chairman of the board of trustees of abington friends school located in montgomery county pennsylvania referencesedit  forbes the worlds billionaires  nicholas schorsch august   shelley schorsch retrieved  january    a b c d the wall street transcript nicholas s schorsch retrieved  january    investment program association biography of nicholas s schorsch retrieved  january    american realty capital ceo nicholas s schorsch receives ernst  young entrepreneur of the year®  lifetime achievement award in greater philadelphia retrieved  december    sponsor revamps compensation retrieved  january    phillycom irvin g schorsch jr april    a b to make money from a bank buy the banks buildings retrieved  january    american financial ceo on reit ipo retrieved  january    banking reits founder ousted retrieved  january    reit sponsor changes name retrieved  january    a b talking nontraded reits with nick schorsch of american realty capital retrieved  december    american realty capital trust joins nasdaq retrieved  december    realty income closes american realty capital trust acquisition retrieved  january    a b american realty offers brokerdealer system to other nontraded reits retrieved  january    a b rcs capital corporation announces milestone  billion lifetime direct investment equity capital raised retrieved  january    a b c new york reit gets public listing in latest for schorsch retrieved  april    dark horse snares one worldwide plaza for b retrieved  april    american realty capital nyrr to acquire  broadway retrieved  april    ventas to acquire american realty capital healthcare reit for  billion in stock and cash retrieved june     rcs capital corporation retrieved  january    rcs capital ipo retrieved  january    first allied holdings inc to be acquired by rcap holdings llc retrieved  january    rcs capital purchase of hatteras sec k retrieved  january    hatteras funds retrieved  january    rcs capital investors capital announcement s